#1. Recursion helps us in solving bigger/complex problems in a simple way. We can convert recursion soln into iteration and vice-versa.
#2. Two types:
       1. Linear Recursion(Fibonacci Series): F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2)
       2. Divide & Conquer Recursion(Binary Search): F(n) = F(n/2) + O(1)

#3. Questions:
              1. Basic Recursion Questions
                    (i). Sum Of Digits
                    (ii). Reverse a number
                    (iii). Fibonacci Series
              2. Array Questions
                    (i). Array Sorted or not
              3. Pattern and Sorting Questions
                    (i). sorting using recursion
              4. Recursion Subset, Subsequence, String, Questions(Processed and unprocessed)
                    (i). skip a character
                    (ii). Subsequence
                    (iii). Subsequence using iterative
              5. Recursion Permutations Questions(all combination)
                    (i). Permutations
              6. Good/Better Recursion Questions
                    (i). Letter Combinations -Leetcode-17
                    (ii). Dice Element Sum

#4. Some imp. things:
            1. str.startsWith("app")
            2. str.isEmpty()
            3. str.substring(1)
            4. ArrayList<Integer>inner = new ArrayList<>(outer.get(i)); //outer.get(i): create the copy of outer ArrayList element into inner ArrayList